.TH "ipr_biosparam" 9 "ipr_biosparam" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipr_biosparam \- Return the HSC mapping
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ipr_biosparam
.BI "(struct scsi_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "struct block_device *block_device "  ","
.BI "sector_t capacity "  ","
.BI "int *parm "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
scsi device struct
.IP "block_device" 12
block device pointer
.IP "capacity" 12
capacity of the device
.IP "parm" 12
Array containing returned HSC values.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function generates the HSC parms that fdisk uses.
We want to make sure we return something that places partitions
on 4k boundaries for best performance with the IOA.

Return value:
0 on success
